  "title": "Vocal Coach",
  "description": "<p>Hark Music, an esteemed institution established in 1999, is renowned for its focus on the Contemporary Pop genre in both English and Mandarin. We are committed to providing enriching experiences beyond the classroom through our HarkLearners’ Portal, multimedia learning materials, OpenStage event, Voice of Hark singing contest, and vocal recording experiences. Catering to learners aged 12 and above, we are on the lookout for talented and passionate Vocal Coaches to join our dynamic team.</p>\n<h2>About the Role</h2>\n<p>As a music coach at Hark Music, you'll not only be sharing your love for music but also empowering others to express themselves through music. You'll be trained and equipped with our EXPRESSWAY® teaching system, designed to enable you to become a proficient coach.</p>\n<h2>Key Responsibilities</h2>\n<ol>\n  <li>Effectively communicate and demonstrate musical techniques to learners, offering constructive feedback to help them improve.</li>\n  <li>Leverage your wide vocal range and knowledge of Pop songs to provide engaging and informative lessons.</li>\n  <li>Share your personal experiences and knowledge gained from years of performing and teaching.</li>\n</ol>\n<h2>What We're Looking For</h2>\n<p>We're seeking individuals who are passionate about music and enjoy coaching others. Candidate should have an extensive vocal range and a minimum of 2 years in performing or teaching experience.</p>\n<h2>Why Join Hark Music?</h2>\n<p>At Hark Music, we believe in the joy of learning and the power of music. We promote personal growth and empowerment, fostering a nurturing and supportive environment for both our staff and learners. As part of our team, you'll play a key role in guiding our learners in their journey of creative self-expression and meaningful skill development.</p>\n<p>So, if you're passionate about music and love the idea of inspiring others to find their voice, we can't wait to hear from you.</p>",
